chairs and tables.

4
00:03:30,419 --> 00:03:33,780
Two women come out with robes.

5
00:03:34,220 --> 00:03:37,740
Their eyes are closed.
Like two sleepwalkers.

6
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:42,300
You get scared... They trip
on everything, poor them.

7
00:03:42,621 --> 00:03:46,141
But suddenly, a man appears.

8
00:03:46,581 --> 00:03:51,061
With a very sad face, the
saddest I have ever seen.

9
00:03:51,541 --> 00:03:55,182
He pushes tables and chairs
out of their way.

10
00:03:57,062 --> 00:04:00,102
You can't imagine how touching
it was.

11
00:04:01,543 --> 00:04:05,143
Someone was sitting next to me.
In his 40s, handsome.

12
00:04:06,223 --> 00:04:09,543
He cried with emotion,
lots of times.

13
00:04:09,823 --> 00:04:13,704
I don't understand why...
It was very beautiful!

14
00:04:15,264 --> 00:04:17,384
I have a surprise for you!

15
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:28,545
I have an autograph of
Rina Baus for you.

16
00:04:28,826 --> 00:04:31,306
I had to buy the photo.

17
00:04:33,666 --> 00:04:35,976
It is in english and says:

18
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:39,387
I hope you surpass all
the obstacles...

19
00:04:39,827 --> 00:04:42,187
...and start dancing.

20
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:09,630
- She has her period.
- It's early.

21
00:06:17,997 --> 00:06:19,717
Good evening.

22
00:06:25,638 --> 00:06:28,278
Benigno, can you
stay tonight?

23
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:31,879
My sister can't,
and I don't have anyone else.

24
00:06:32,159 --> 00:06:34,959
Why did you come?
You should have called.

25
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:38,560
I am not taking advantage of you.
This week you did 3 nights.

26
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:42,680
Don't worry. A free afternoon
is enough for me.

27
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,480
I have to see the house
workers. It's a mess.

28
00:06:48,321 --> 00:06:50,791
And to frame a photo.

29
00:06:50,841 --> 00:06:55,121
My condition is not improving.
The hospital will decide.

30
00:06:55,641 --> 00:06:58,602
Your husband left you
and the children.

31
00:06:58,882 --> 00:07:02,482
Just come the nights you can.
We will be ok.

32
00:07:05,202 --> 00:07:07,163
Thanks a lot.

33
00:07:08,363 --> 00:07:11,723
- You cut off the intestinal food.
- She couldn't take it.

34
00:07:11,963 --> 00:07:15,123
- We will try again tomorrow.
- Yes, go now.

35
00:07:16,404 --> 00:07:18,324
And keep the spirits up!

36
00:07:25,365 --> 00:07:30,045
Six bulls and a woman.
Wednesday at Briuega.

37
00:07:31,205 --> 00:07:34,846
Lydia P Gonzales will
fight six bulls.

38
00:07:36,646 --> 00:07:39,326
Why such a drastic decision?

39
00:07:39,446 --> 00:07:42,966
It's my job. 2 bulls, or 6.
Whatever they say.

40
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:46,607
People say a lot of bullfighters
won't fight with you...

41
00:07:46,657 --> 00:07:48,912
...because you are a woman.

42
00:07:48,962 --> 00:07:51,167
People can say what they want.

43
00:07:51,487 --> 00:07:54,888
Too much chauvinism in bullfighting,
but there are exceptions.

44
00:07:55,288 --> 00:08:00,048
Nino Valencia was happy to share
billing with you for several months.

45
00:08:03,009 --> 00:08:05,969
Do you think he did it
to promote himself?

46
00:08:06,329 --> 00:08:08,569
And when he succeeded that,
he abandoned you?

47
00:08:08,849 --> 00:08:11,770
I told you, I don't want
to talk about this!

48
00:08:12,090 --> 00:08:14,970
But by talking about
certain problems...

49
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,850
...is the first step
towards their solution.

50
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:20,451
- Nino Valencia...
- Enough!

51
00:08:20,811 --> 00:08:24,411
My dear Lydia, let me
finish the question.

52
00:08:24,461 --> 00:08:28,011
I am not discussing this.
I told you earlier.

53
00:08:28,131 --> 00:08:32,372
You didn't say anything earlier!
It's bad what you are saying!

54
00:08:32,422 --> 00:08:35,402
They will think
it's a fixed interview.

55
00:08:35,452 --> 00:08:39,253
And I am on of the few who
dare say the truth...

56
00:08:39,453 --> 00:08:42,363
...and you should dare accept

57
00:08:42,413 --> 00:08:45,613
...that Nino Valencia
took advantage of you.

58
00:08:46,013 --> 00:08:50,494
He shared with you not only
the fame, but sex as well.

59
00:08:50,544 --> 00:08:53,934
And he left you when
time was right.

60
00:08:55,294 --> 00:08:58,335
Juan Luis, Marco here...
How are you?

61
00:08:58,935 --> 00:09:01,095
I want to ask you something.

62
00:09:01,775 --> 00:09:05,215
I would like to do an article
about Lydia Gonzales.

63
00:09:06,135 --> 00:09:08,336
Yes, I see it too...

64
00:09:10,976 --> 00:09:13,736
I would like to do something
deep.

65
00:09:15,657 --> 00:09:18,817
For the Sunday issue?
Great...

66
00:10:12,783 --> 00:10:16,663
- The woman has gone crazy!
- She dedicates it to you.

67
00:10:17,063 --> 00:10:20,744
She would let the bull injur
her, just so that you see it.

68
00:10:21,264 --> 00:10:24,264
You shouldn't have come,
especially you.

69
00:11:13,189 --> 00:11:16,190
Don't tell me anything.
I know what I am doing.

70
00:11:16,630 --> 00:11:20,550
Nino should concentrate.
He doesn't want any more worries.

71
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:24,790
Nothing to worry about. He should
just come to pick up his stuff.

72
00:11:25,511 --> 00:11:29,231
- Or tell me where to send them.
- Send them at my place.

73
00:11:29,281 --> 00:11:32,951
He, himself, should say so.
This is nothing to do with you.

74
00:11:35,392 --> 00:11:37,792
You can leave whenever you want.

75
00:11:38,112 --> 00:11:40,872
- Good evening.
- Scotch on the rocks, please.

76
00:11:40,922 --> 00:11:44,113
- What glass do you prefer?
- A tall one.

77
00:11:48,713 --> 00:11:51,713
Can I talk to you for
a minute, please?

78
00:11:53,394 --> 00:11:56,554
Forget it. When something is
over, it's over.

79
00:11:58,074 --> 00:12:01,714
- What are you saying?
- Can I talk to you?

80
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:07,995
If you take me to Madrid,
we can talk on the way.

81
00:12:08,045 --> 00:12:10,115
It will be my pleasure.

82
00:12:22,797 --> 00:12:26,037
- Who named you Lydia;
- My father.

83
00:12:26,277 --> 00:12:29,397
It's as if he sealed your destiny.

84
00:12:29,517 --> 00:12:33,798
He always wanted to be a bullfighter,
but stayed a banderillero.

85
00:12:34,518 --> 00:12:38,198
He is the one that was there
for me, more than anyone else.

86
00:12:38,638 --> 00:12:40,919
But he died last year.

87
00:12:42,199 --> 00:12:44,159
I am sorry.

88
00:12:44,799 --> 00:12:48,159
'El Pais' wants me to do a profile
on you for their Sunday issue.

89
00:12:48,439 --> 00:12:51,800
Do you write on bullfighting?
I don't know your name.

90
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:55,200
To be honest,
I know nothing of it.

91
00:12:56,400 --> 00:13:00,081
But I know a lot about
desperate women.

92
00:13:00,481 --> 00:13:03,761
And who told you I am
desperate?

93
00:13:04,081 --> 00:13:07,522
- This is the impression I have.
- Bullfighting doesn't interest you.

94
00:13:07,572 --> 00:13:10,562
You are interested in my
relationship with Nino Valencia.

95
00:13:10,842 --> 00:13:13,882
Tell El Pais to leave me alone!

96
00:13:51,686 --> 00:13:54,247
- Take me from here!
- What's going on?

97
00:13:54,327 --> 00:13:57,967
Take me from here! There is
a snake in the kitchen.

98
00:13:58,287 --> 00:14:01,327
- Give me the keys.
- The door is open.

99
00:14:01,607 --> 00:14:03,808
Calm down.
And stay there.

100
00:15:33,977 --> 00:15:35,978
My purse.

101
00:15:37,818 --> 00:15:40,258
Take me to a hotel.

102
00:15:40,618 --> 00:15:43,298
I am never coming back to
this house.

103
00:15:44,018 --> 00:15:47,659
- To which hotel?
- To Eurobuilding, lets say.

104
00:16:16,262 --> 00:16:19,462
Don't tell anyone about
the snake, please.

105
00:16:20,342 --> 00:16:22,983
Only my family knows.

106
00:16:23,103 --> 00:16:26,343
I always respect other
people's phobias.

107
00:16:26,703 --> 00:16:30,824
After what you have done, how
can I say no to the profile?

108
00:16:31,584 --> 00:16:35,544
Think about it again. I will
call tomorrow, tell me then.

109
00:16:36,344 --> 00:16:38,624
Thanks for everything.

110
00:17:00,867 --> 00:17:04,667
Do you want me to stay? I can
sleep in the sofa.

111
00:17:04,867 --> 00:17:08,028
No, I need to get used to
being alone.

112
00:17:48,952 --> 00:17:50,832
Do you wash her?

113
00:17:51,112 --> 00:17:52,992
What do you think?

114
00:17:53,672 --> 00:17:56,313
- How was the night?
- Normal.

115
00:17:56,713 --> 00:18:00,273
- Give it to me. I will do it.
- I am going now.

116
00:18:00,473 --> 00:18:02,753
- Good bye.
- Bye, Matilde.

117
00:18:06,114 --> 00:18:08,114
It's so hot!

118
00:18:08,554 --> 00:18:12,114
- Lets cut her hair.
- short, it's more practical.

119
00:18:13,035 --> 00:18:16,075
We will leave it as it was
when she came here...

120
00:18:16,355 --> 00:18:19,235
...so that she is not surprised
when she wakes up.

121
00:18:19,285 --> 00:18:22,236
After 4 years, it will be great.

122
00:18:22,316 --> 00:18:24,796
I believe in miracles.
So should you.

123
00:18:24,846 --> 00:18:27,796
- Why me?
- Because you need them.

124
00:18:28,036 --> 00:18:32,077
One might happen to you,
and you will not know.

125
00:18:32,797 --> 00:18:34,837
So hot!

126
00:18:35,077 --> 00:18:37,107
I took something from the
drugstore...

127
00:18:37,157 --> 00:18:40,158
...to help stop the perspiration
stains on my uniform.

128
00:18:40,558 --> 00:18:43,998
My armpits are ok,
but look at my face.

129
00:18:44,048 --> 00:18:46,358
- What's it called?
- Perspirex.

130
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:57,239
It's Marco...
Remember me?

131
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:57,800
- Sure.

132
00:18:57,999 --> 00:19:00,440
- How are you?
- Naked.

133
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:08,561
I need to buy some clothes.
That's all I've got.

134
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:11,521
I can bring you some
from your place.

135
00:19:11,881 --> 00:19:14,961
I don't want anything from there.
Maybe another time.

136
00:19:15,281 --> 00:19:17,402
- Where are we going?
- To Sybilla.

137
00:19:17,642 --> 00:19:20,082
- You think I am crazy.
- Why?

138
00:19:20,362 --> 00:19:23,842
- Because I don't want to go home.
- No, I understand.

139
00:19:24,282 --> 00:19:28,403
When I separated, I couldn't
sleep in the same bed...

140
00:19:28,763 --> 00:19:31,803
I was sleeping in the sofa,
in the living room.

141
00:19:32,003 --> 00:19:36,204
For a week. Until I finally
bought a new bed.

142
00:19:36,604 --> 00:19:38,724
So, you are separated.

143
00:19:39,484 --> 00:19:41,364
I am alone.

144
00:19:42,284 --> 00:19:45,885
AFTER A FEW MONTHS

145
00:20:03,086 --> 00:20:05,767
Marco, we should
talk afterwards.

146
00:20:06,087 --> 00:20:09,527
- We've been talking for an hour.
- You have, not me.

147
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:12,447
Indeed.

148
00:20:40,050 --> 00:20:44,411
Did you read about the nuns
that got raped by the misionaries?

149
00:20:46,051 --> 00:20:49,772
Priests, themselves!
It's horrible!

150
00:20:50,292 --> 00:20:53,172
Yeah, they've gone bad too!
Where are we heading to?

151
00:20:53,222 --> 00:20:55,652
First they raped the locals.

152
00:20:56,092 --> 00:20:59,373
Then, due to AIDS, they started
raping nuns.

153
00:21:00,293 --> 00:21:02,933
And I admired them so much!

154
00:21:03,293 --> 00:21:05,933
Not all of them are rapists,
for sure.

155
00:21:06,253 --> 00:21:08,974
No, some of them are
pedophiles.

156
00:21:09,334 --> 00:21:12,974
- What's that? Everyone loves fucking.
- Antonio, you are an animal!

157
00:21:14,774 --> 00:21:17,735
- How do the bulls look?
- Good, but fat.

158
00:21:18,215 --> 00:21:21,295
- How much do you think?
- Over 500 kilos.

159
00:21:22,095 --> 00:21:25,775
I am going to the bar. And don't
forget, we are eating home.

160
00:21:26,095 --> 00:21:29,376
If the kids don't see their aunt,
there'll be hell to pay.

161
00:24:41,797 --> 00:24:44,477
Don't cry, my love.

162
00:24:53,998 --> 00:24:56,878
- How is it?
- Very bad.

163
00:24:56,928 --> 00:24:58,678
It tore her apart.

164
00:24:58,758 --> 00:25:01,229
The father will be happy now!

165
00:25:01,279 --> 00:25:05,479
'Not the little one!', we kept
telling him, my mother and I.

166
00:25:07,919 --> 00:25:10,720
And yet, she became like him.

167
00:25:10,770 --> 00:25:12,960
Don't be upset.

168
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:16,000
What time is it?

169
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,321
It has been four hours.

170
00:25:19,641 --> 00:25:22,481
AFTER THREE WEEKS

171
00:25:23,801 --> 00:25:25,871
Are you going to Cordoba?

172
00:25:25,921 --> 00:25:29,562
Yes... I would like to stay,
but I can't.

173
00:25:29,642 --> 00:25:33,082
We can't do anything extra.

174
00:25:33,202 --> 00:25:35,552
The bar's been closed for 20 days.

175
00:25:35,602 --> 00:25:39,043
The kids are with the neigbhour,
and I've neglected the other one.

176
00:25:39,323 --> 00:25:42,723
If something happens, can
you be here in 2 hours?

177
00:25:43,163 --> 00:25:47,164
- Rest assured for that.
- We have to have faith.

178
00:25:49,204 --> 00:25:51,794
I light some candles...

179
00:25:51,844 --> 00:25:54,764
...but I find it very
difficult to have faith.

180
00:25:55,445 --> 00:25:58,565
When can we put her medals
back on her?

181
00:25:59,565 --> 00:26:01,395
Not yet.

182
00:26:01,445 --> 00:26:05,566
With all these...
wounds, the tracheotomy...

183
00:26:08,486 --> 00:26:10,686
She never took them off.

184
00:26:24,328 --> 00:26:26,368
I will get a vase.

185
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:48,490
I have to go to the US
for three months.

186
00:26:48,970 --> 00:26:52,051
It is very important,
says my agent.

187
00:26:52,371 --> 00:26:56,251
And yet... the way things
stand here...

188
00:26:59,051 --> 00:27:01,492
...I don't want to go.

189
00:27:14,133 --> 00:27:17,173
Can you get out for
a moment, please?

190
00:27:26,334 --> 00:27:29,295
No smoking here.

191
00:27:31,815 --> 00:27:34,015
Did she talk to you that day?

192
00:27:35,775 --> 00:27:39,056
- Or rather, I talked.
- And what did you say?

193
00:27:40,416 --> 00:27:42,456
Things that concern me.

194
00:27:43,256 --> 00:27:46,086
Did she tell you anything
about me?

195
00:27:46,136 --> 00:27:50,097
Honestly, Lydia hadn't talked
about you for a long time.

196
00:27:50,937 --> 00:27:55,297
- It's my fault for what happened.
- No, it's my fault.

197
00:31:52,483 --> 00:31:55,523
Caetano made me
freak out.

198
00:31:58,764 --> 00:32:02,284
Marco, I've always wanted
to ask you something.

199
00:32:02,524 --> 00:32:06,205
Why did you cry that night,
after you killed the snake?

200
00:32:07,925 --> 00:32:10,325
It brought me lots of memories.

201
00:32:12,005 --> 00:32:15,486
Years ago, I had to
kill another snake.

202
00:32:15,846 --> 00:32:17,966
We were in Africa.

203
00:32:18,406 --> 00:32:21,356
She had the same phobia as you.

204
00:32:21,406 --> 00:32:26,447
She was waiting outside the tent,
terrified, defenseless...

205
00:32:27,767 --> 00:32:30,007
...and totally naked...

206
00:32:31,647 --> 00:32:34,928
...because she had seen the snake,
while we were asleep.

207
00:32:35,288 --> 00:32:38,448
Was it the same one who made
you sleep in the living room?

208
00:32:40,768 --> 00:32:43,129
I hate that woman.

209
00:32:43,569 --> 00:32:47,089
- I haven't seen her for years.
- Even worse.

210
00:32:47,139 --> 00:32:50,089
What can I do to make you
forget her?

211
00:32:50,289 --> 00:32:52,650
Exactly what you are doing now.

212
00:33:22,213 --> 00:33:25,973
You were sound asleep. We didn't
want to wake you up.

213
00:33:27,853 --> 00:33:31,454
- Is Dr Vega here?
- He is in his office.

214
00:34:11,818 --> 00:34:14,899
Rosa, close the door.
There's a draft.

215
00:34:15,659 --> 00:34:18,779
- She opened her eyes.
- That gives me the creeps!

216
00:34:19,059 --> 00:34:22,099
- And when she yawns?
- I shit myself!

217
00:34:23,939 --> 00:34:27,060
Good morning, doctor.
I want to talk to you.

218
00:34:27,620 --> 00:34:29,900
How are you? Did you sleep well?

219
00:34:30,820 --> 00:34:32,380
I will buy you coffee.

220
00:34:34,061 --> 00:34:37,261
How long for might Lydia
stay like that?

221
00:34:37,541 --> 00:34:41,221
Months... years...
maybe for the rest of her life...

222
00:34:42,181 --> 00:34:44,542
There is no hope?

223
00:34:45,942 --> 00:34:49,382
As a doctor, I have to say
no... However...

224
00:34:49,662 --> 00:34:51,622
RESUSCITATION

225
00:34:52,023 --> 00:34:55,383
Meryl Moon wakes up after
15 years in a coma.

226
00:34:55,703 --> 00:34:58,773
She went into a coma during
childbirth.

227
00:34:58,823 --> 00:35:03,104
Meryl was a PVS, persistent
vegetative state, like Lydia, for life.

228
00:35:03,944 --> 00:35:07,104
Her recovery contradicts
everything I am about to say.

229
00:35:07,154 --> 00:35:09,024
That is, that there is hope.

230
00:35:09,424 --> 00:35:11,775
I insist. Scientifically, no.

231
00:35:11,825 --> 00:35:14,945
But if you want to have faith,
OK.

232
00:35:15,265 --> 00:35:18,535
Is she opening her eyes?
Or I imagine this?

233
00:35:18,585 --> 00:35:22,986
She does, but that doesn't mean
she is aware of anything.

234
00:35:23,506 --> 00:35:27,386
Her brain cells has been
completely destroyed.

235
00:35:27,906 --> 00:35:32,507
However, it can control
the automatic functions...

236
00:35:32,907 --> 00:35:37,307
such as breathing, sleeping,
waking up and intestinal functions.

237
00:35:37,357 --> 00:35:40,058
She opens her eyes,
but mechanically.

238
00:35:40,108 --> 00:35:43,348
Her brain is dead. She has
no ideas and feelings.

239
00:35:57,670 --> 00:36:00,070
Come in, please.

240
00:36:11,351 --> 00:36:14,351
- My name is Benigno.
- Marco Zuloaga

241
00:36:14,511 --> 00:36:16,592
This is Alicia.

