more subtle.

275
00:39:21,532 --> 00:39:24,572
- What is my orientation?
- And what did you say?

276
00:39:24,622 --> 00:39:27,172
- That I like men.
- Really?

277
00:39:27,732 --> 00:39:30,213
No, you fool. I lied.

278
00:39:30,493 --> 00:39:33,813
How can he dare ask whether
I like men or women?

279
00:39:34,053 --> 00:39:37,053
- What does he care?
- I am glad I found out.

280
00:39:37,413 --> 00:39:42,174
Did he ask the head nurse or you
if you like bestiality or coprophagy?

281
00:39:42,494 --> 00:39:46,134
No, you are right. They don't
ask such things.

282
00:39:53,495 --> 00:39:58,056
I might go on a trip, and I won't
be able to come and see you.

283
00:39:58,816 --> 00:40:02,576
But, in Geneva, they've
offered me a creation...

284
00:40:02,626 --> 00:40:05,606
...a chorography
that thrills me.

285
00:40:05,656 --> 00:40:09,377
An old idea for a ballet.
I call it 'Trenches'.

286
00:40:09,457 --> 00:40:12,537
It is about the first
world war.

287
00:40:12,817 --> 00:40:15,417
I will need a lot of dancers...

288
00:40:15,497 --> 00:40:19,418
...because in the war there
are a lot of soldiers.

289
00:40:19,738 --> 00:40:24,258
But everyone dances in Geneva.
It is great.

290
00:40:24,658 --> 00:40:29,179
I want female dancers too, because
the soldier when dying...

291
00:40:29,229 --> 00:40:33,019
...lets his soul
get out of his body...

292
00:40:33,299 --> 00:40:36,980
...the ghost of which
will be a female dancer.

293
00:40:37,620 --> 00:40:41,020
With a white classic skirt
like 'Giselle'...

294
00:40:41,070 --> 00:40:44,781
...but with red stains of blood.

295
00:40:44,831 --> 00:40:46,131
Very good!

296
00:40:46,181 --> 00:40:48,171
Alicia loved it.

297
00:40:48,221 --> 00:40:52,261
It's good because life emerges
out of death.

298
00:40:52,982 --> 00:40:56,182
the female emerges from
the male.

299
00:40:56,702 --> 00:40:59,502
And from the earthly emerges the...

300
00:41:02,703 --> 00:41:05,303
The beach?

301
00:41:06,943 --> 00:41:09,743
And from the earthly emerges the...

302
00:41:10,263 --> 00:41:12,264
The water?

303
00:41:13,064 --> 00:41:14,984
The ethereal.

304
00:41:15,584 --> 00:41:19,104
The ethereal...
the imperceptible, the spirit.

305
00:41:20,024 --> 00:41:24,065
I have the music. It is from
Kristof Penderesky.

306
00:41:24,625 --> 00:41:28,305
It was written for the victims
of Hiroshima, but it's OK.

307
00:41:28,545 --> 00:41:31,506
Of course. Alicia remembers
it perfectly well.

308
00:41:31,866 --> 00:41:35,986
It's music for the battle.
It's wild and beastly.

309
00:41:36,306 --> 00:41:40,027
And regarding the music during deaths
I have a masterpiece...

310
00:41:40,077 --> 00:41:43,467
...which you will listen to,
right now.

311
00:41:45,787 --> 00:41:48,308
It will drive you crazy.

312
00:41:54,588 --> 00:41:56,948
Alicia, my dear.

313
00:41:57,388 --> 00:41:59,829
Good bye, my dear.

314
00:42:08,190 --> 00:42:11,830
Good bye, Katerina.
And you look beautiful.

315
00:42:11,990 --> 00:42:15,190
- You should go ahead with 'Trenches'.
- I will.

316
00:42:29,232 --> 00:42:32,552
Look... We will place you
next to the window.

317
00:42:33,872 --> 00:42:37,233
You will be able to see your
friends dancing.

318
00:42:42,713 --> 00:42:44,714
I love this room.

319
00:42:45,874 --> 00:42:47,994
I will order everything.

320
00:42:53,835 --> 00:42:56,755
Come in and shut the door...

321
00:43:02,516 --> 00:43:05,196
How are you?... Sit down.

322
00:43:05,676 --> 00:43:08,106
Alicia, look who's here.

323
00:43:08,156 --> 00:43:10,996
We're just getting some air,
reading magazines...

324
00:43:12,877 --> 00:43:15,957
Who was the lady that just left?

325
00:43:16,007 --> 00:43:18,677
Katerina, Alicia's teacher.

326
00:43:19,717 --> 00:43:22,198
Dancing teacher.

327
00:43:22,718 --> 00:43:24,718
Nice character, Katerina.

328
00:43:24,798 --> 00:43:28,198
She has a dancing school somewhere
here. Alicia was her student.

329
00:43:28,438 --> 00:43:31,519
And Katerina loves her like
her daughter.

330
00:43:39,400 --> 00:43:42,320
