333
00:45:06,409 --> 00:45:08,569
What's the matter? Are you
following me?

334
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,690
This is yours, I think.
It must have dropped you.

335
00:45:19,250 --> 00:45:22,451
Is everything there?...
I didn't touch anything...

336
00:45:24,251 --> 00:45:26,921
- Where are you going?
- Home.

337
00:45:26,971 --> 00:45:30,281
Can I accompany you?
I have nothing else to do.

338
00:45:30,331 --> 00:45:34,412
- Yes, but I am going home.
- Of course... It will do me good.

339
00:45:34,652 --> 00:45:37,812
Dancing is my life.
I love dancing shows.

340
00:45:37,862 --> 00:45:40,973
- Do you like dancing?
- Yes, of course

341
00:45:41,023 --> 00:45:43,243
But I don't follow it.

342
00:45:43,293 --> 00:45:45,933
What else do you do,
besides dancing?

343
00:45:45,983 --> 00:45:49,734
I travel and watch old movies.

344
00:45:50,054 --> 00:45:53,894
Silent Cinema is attractive
to me, in particular.

345
00:45:55,654 --> 00:45:58,535
- Where do you go when you go out?
- I don't.

346
00:45:58,615 --> 00:46:00,645
You should go out.

347
00:46:00,695 --> 00:46:03,975
I was taking care of my mother,
but she passed away 2 months ago.

348
00:46:04,255 --> 00:46:07,776
I am sorry. Mine died too,
years ago though.

349
00:46:09,176 --> 00:46:12,776
Here we are...
Thanks for the wallet.

350
00:46:39,979 --> 00:46:43,299
Dr Roncero, psychiatrist.
7th left.

351
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:48,380
Twenty three.

352
00:46:50,260 --> 00:46:53,901
I was waiting for her by the window,
but that day she didn't come.

353
00:46:54,621 --> 00:46:58,581
But I knew her address and that
her father was a psychiatrist.

354
00:47:06,382 --> 00:47:08,742
Dr Roncero's office.

355
00:47:09,422 --> 00:47:12,423
I would like to make an
appointment.

356
00:47:12,943 --> 00:47:16,383
- Is it tomorrow at 5 OK?
- Isn't earlier possible?

357
00:47:16,663 --> 00:47:18,863
No, tomorrow at 5.

358
00:47:19,143 --> 00:47:21,063
Your name?

359
00:47:37,505 --> 00:47:41,306
- What do you want?
- I have an appointment at 5.

360
00:47:50,067 --> 00:47:52,587
Come in. Don't stand there.

361
00:47:58,828 --> 00:48:02,468
Benigno Martin?...
I need some information.

362
00:48:04,348 --> 00:48:08,509
<i>I just wanted to see Alicia,
but I was there, at a psychiatrist.</i>

363
00:48:08,829 --> 00:48:11,749
<i>I decided to tell him I missed
my mother.</i>

364
00:48:14,229 --> 00:48:17,350
I started when I was little.

365
00:48:17,670 --> 00:48:22,030
And all those 15 years
you took care of your mother?

366
00:48:22,990 --> 00:48:27,391
I was always next to her...
I was studying to be a nurse.

367
00:48:27,791 --> 00:48:31,071
I was only going out to the
classes.

368
00:48:31,151 --> 00:48:35,311
I was also studying aesthetics,
make-up and hairdressing.

369
00:48:35,361 --> 00:48:37,752
But those by post.

370
00:48:38,032 --> 00:48:41,632
So you did those on your mother?

371
00:48:42,032 --> 00:48:45,553
Of course, and I cut her hair,
dyed it, did her nails.

372
00:48:45,603 --> 00:48:48,593
And I scrubbed her down well,
front and back.

373
00:48:48,993 --> 00:48:52,113
My mother wasn't disabled, or mad.

374
00:48:52,273 --> 00:48:54,714
She was only a bit lazy.

375
00:48:55,674 --> 00:48:59,434
She was a beautiful woman
and I didn't want to let herself go.

376
00:49:00,074 --> 00:49:03,515
- What did your father say?
- Nothing. What could he?

377
00:49:03,755 --> 00:49:06,635
- Is he dead?
- God, no.

378
00:49:07,035 --> 00:49:11,715
He is in Sweden, I guess.
I haven't heard from him for years.

379
00:49:12,035 --> 00:49:14,476
Doesn't he come to see you?

380
00:49:15,516 --> 00:49:19,796
He has his own family there,
after he left my mother.

381
00:49:22,317 --> 00:49:24,957
We are not in touch.

382
00:49:25,237 --> 00:49:28,277
Why did you come to see me,
Benigno?

383
00:49:29,517 --> 00:49:32,508
- What's your problem?
- Me? Nothing.

384
00:49:32,558 --> 00:49:36,678
You must have since you came
to see a psychiatrist.

385
00:49:39,278 --> 00:49:41,839
Loneliness, I guess.

386
00:49:44,479 --> 00:49:47,679
Have you had a sexual
relationship with a woman?

387
00:49:49,479 --> 00:49:52,320
- With a man?
- No, neither.

388
00:49:54,640 --> 00:49:57,400
I will see you in a week.

389
00:49:57,760 --> 00:50:01,301
- Am I not well doctor?
- That's not it...

390
00:50:01,351 --> 00:50:04,876
However, your adolescence was
kind of special.

391
00:50:04,926 --> 00:50:08,402
- It wasn't special.
- It was. Very special.

392
00:50:09,762 --> 00:50:12,602
And we must analyse it in depth.

393
00:50:12,652 --> 00:50:14,722
Yes, lets analyse it.

394
00:50:19,443 --> 00:50:22,563
- Should I come in a week?
- Very well.

395
00:50:23,283 --> 00:50:25,363
I am glad.

396
00:51:54,093 --> 00:51:57,813
- What are you doing here?
- I was just going. Don't be angry.

397
00:51:58,293 --> 00:52:02,334
I just wanted to see you...
But I am harmless.

398
00:52:18,696 --> 00:52:22,336
Dr Roncero's office...
Hi, Lola...

399
00:52:22,696 --> 00:52:26,536
I just had a shit of
huge dimensions.

400
00:53:12,741 --> 00:53:15,382
Can you be in charge?

401
00:53:30,983 --> 00:53:34,984
Alicia never came back. I
didn't want to scare her again.

402
00:53:35,344 --> 00:53:38,984
After a week I went to her
place, to see her father.

403
00:53:39,864 --> 00:53:42,545
It was raining during that
whole week.

404
00:53:48,785 --> 00:53:51,746
Next time I saw her was here.

405
00:53:51,796 --> 00:53:53,466
What happened to her?

406
00:53:53,546 --> 00:53:56,626
A car accident,
during a rainy day.

407
00:53:57,946 --> 00:54:01,947
Her father didn't want her to
be alone, not even for a moment.

408
00:54:02,027 --> 00:54:04,547
He asked for the best nurses.

409
00:54:04,707 --> 00:54:09,308
And I have a good reputation here...
So they suggested me...

410
00:54:09,708 --> 00:54:14,628
And when he saw me, he remembered
me, and hesitated for a moment.

411
00:54:15,028 --> 00:54:18,589
But in the end, he took
Matilde and me, exclusively.

412
00:54:18,869 --> 00:54:22,629
And this was four years ago...
And here we are now...

413
00:54:22,869 --> 00:54:24,549
Right, Alicia?

414
00:54:28,910 --> 00:54:32,270
I started going to the ballet,
when I had a day-off.

415
00:54:32,320 --> 00:54:35,870
And to the film library to watch
silent movies.

416
00:54:36,030 --> 00:54:39,351
German, American, Italian
films, everything.

417
00:54:39,631 --> 00:54:42,671
And afterwards I would tell her
about all that she had seen.

418
00:54:43,831 --> 00:54:47,272
The four most complete years
of my life.

419
00:54:47,322 --> 00:54:49,422
I take care of Alicia...

420
00:54:49,472 --> 00:54:53,232
I do what she would, except
the trips, of course.

421
00:54:53,472 --> 00:54:56,473
With me and Lydia
it's the opposite.

422
00:54:58,473 --> 00:55:00,793
I can't touch her.

423
00:55:03,113 --> 00:55:05,994
I don't recognize her body.

424
00:55:06,154 --> 00:55:10,074
